summary: Killing Eve is about a talented female assassin and the British intelligence officer trying to find her. The two are equally...
caption:
Killing Eve is about a talented female assassin and the British intelligence officer trying to find her. The two are equally obsessed with each other, and that is what sells the show. There’s a dangerous tension between the two. I can’t do it justice in this review, you’ve just got to watch.

This is a slick espionage show with brutal deaths. I typically watched this show before bed, and a few of Villanelle’s assassinations were still on my mind when I woke up in the morning. Despite the inherent gayness of the premise, this show (spoilers) still buries its most openly gay character. That trope continues to be upsetting and frankly mind-boggling. Kill off a straight for once. 

Despite that, I’m still kind of in love with this show and its characters. Shoutout to Sandra Oh’s curly hair.
